init_oa_default_rule(25.10)                        init_oa_default_rule(25.10)

Name
       init_oa_default_rule

Syntax
       init_oa_default_rule <ruleName>

       Specifies  a constraint group name at the start of Innovus session. The
       name provided would be used by Innovus for reading the  place-and-route
       technology rules from the constraint group.

       If the user specified constraint group is not found, Innovus outputs an
       error  during  init_design.  If  no  value  is  specified  for init_de-
       fault_oa_rule, Innovus falls back to the default look-up mechanism  for
       LefDefaultRouteSpec  constraint group used by any place-and-route tool.
       Follow these guidelines while using this parameter:

              * You can set this parameter only at the start of  Innovus  ses-
                sion .

              * You  will need to resolve conflicts in a design arising due to
                the two incompatible constraint groups used in two design runs
                in two different Innovus sessions.

       The specified constraint group must have the following:

              * Valid layers

              * Valid vias

              * Width

              * Spacing

Related Information
              * init_design

